race.comment: PAPER DOLL (8) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up in all seven runs this preparation and this is not an overly strong affair. Has placed three from three over this seven-furlong journey and gets some weight off with the 2kg claim. Can go one better against this line-up. TAM NA GHAR (10) has been well in the betting in both career outings to date and where there's smoke there's fire. Top-three aspirations again. PEAK MISS (9) will be rock-hard fit for this and may earn some minor money. INSIDE PASSAGE (4) is resuming from a lay-off. Fitter for a recent trial at Sunshine Coast Inner Track. Opened last campaign with a ninth at Gold Coast over 1200m. Should be primed for this.
